Legs uniformly light brown, covered with long white seta, especially on ventral surface. Leg I longer and much stouter than the other legs, ventrally filled with leg cuspules from tarsus to femur, except on patella (
Fig. 10C
); metatarsi III and IV distally with a comb-like structure distally, followed by brush of setae. Leg measurements: leg I 5.65 (1.77, 0.66, 1.57, 1.02, 0.63); leg II 5.37 (1.65, 0.52, 1.35, 1.18, 0.67); leg III 3.62 (1.03, 0.36, 0.84, 0.92, 0.47); leg IV 4.91 (1.42, 0.40, 1.27, 1.27, 0.55).

Male palp (
Fig. 11
): Cymbium oval. Bulb round. Tegulum inflated, but not covering RTA in ventral view. RTA long, distally spatulate, ending in sickle-shaped apical claw. Sperm duct visible in ventral view, widely Ushaped. Embolus arising from wide basal part originating from middle of bulb; distal part coiled horizontally, much narrower than bulb, looping once.

